<L>__{exterior town square ramelle day}
<A>__{the sounds of sporadic small arms fire. the town square is a deserted battlefield, littered with burning debris, shell casings and bodies, german and american and a few french civilians. miller and his men enter the square, weapons ready, leap frogging from doorway to doorway. miller and sarge crouch run to the cover of some overhanging debris. they listen, trying to pinpoint the exact source of the firing. sarge motions his guess. miller nods in agreement. he signals for the men to follow him around, not toward, the firing. they move on, dashing from cover to cover.}
